name: df-goel

comment: Define the Godel-set of membership. Here the arguments ` x = <. N , P >. ` correspond to v_N and v_P , so ` ( (/) e.g 1o ) ` actually means v_0 ` e. ` v_1 , not ` 0 e. 1 ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 14-Jul-2013.)
